did.head: DESCRIPTIVE SUMMARY
did.repository: Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library
did.abstract: Files include correspondence with constituents, colleagues, special interest groups and others; memoranda and statistical information; press releases and copies of speeches; printed House and Senate bills and committe reports; and pamphlets and clippings concerning congressional committees, legislation under consideration, and numerous items of public interest, both to the nation as a whole and to his constituency. Also correspondence, deed searches, and other papers, 1919-1946, of the law firm, Taber and Parker, and occasional personal papers of Representative Taber.

bioghist.head: BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE
bioghist.p: Lawyer, legislator; U.S. Congressman from Auburn, New York (1923-1963).

scopecontent.head: COLLECTION DESCRIPTION
scopecontent.p: Files include correspondence with constituents, colleagues, special interest groups and others; memoranda and statistical information; press releases and copies of speeches; printed House and Senate bills and committe reports; and pamphlets and clippings concerning congressional committees, legislation under consideration, and numerous items of public interest, both to the nation as a whole and to his constituency. Also correspondence, deed searches, and other papers, 1919-1946, of the law firm, Taber and Parker, and occasional personal papers of Representative Taber.

prefercite.head: Cite As:
prefercite.p: John Taber papers, #2202. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.
